comments:
In 1894 the part in West Sussex (which 
    until 1.4.1889 had been part of Sussex) became part of the parish of Rogate, 
    so that thereafter Bramshott was entirely in Hampshire. Renamed 24.4.1974 to become 
    the parish of Bramshott & Liphook. See also Table 2, notes (a), (c) and (e).

Created 24.4.1974 by renaming the parish of Bramshott. See also 
    Table 2, notes (i), (j) and (k).
See Table 2, note (k).
See Table 2, notes (f) and (k).

Abolished 1.4.1932 and added to the parish of Colemore & 
    Priors Dean.

Created 1.4.1932 out of the parishes of Priors Dean and Colemore. 
    See also Table 2, note (k).

Created 24.4.1974 by renaming the parish of Eastmeon. See also Table 2, note 
    (k).
Renamed 24.4.1974 to become the parish of East Meon.
Abolished 1.4.1932 and added to the parish of Hawkley.
See Table 2, note (k).

That part which until 1.4.1932 formed part of the parish of Bramshott. 
    See also Table 2, note (e).
See Table 2, notes (d), (j) and (k).
See Table 2, notes (i) and (k).
See Table 2, notes (f) and (k).
